PN,39107
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F391A1778245867
OL,3,CWhat went wrong for Labour in the
OL,4,CNorth West?
OL,6,FThere will be relief within the Labour
OL,7,FParty that the majority of elections
OL,8,Fin the North West were not for all-out
OL,9,Fcontrol.
OL,11,FIn Salford, Labour hung on to the
OL,12,Fmajority it has enjoyed since the
OL,13,Flocal authority was established in its
OL,14,Fcurrent form in 1973. But Reform took
OL,15,F13 of the 21 seats up for election,
OL,16,Fleaving Labour with only 57% of the
OL,17,Ftotal council seats, its lowest share
OL,18,Fsince 1978.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/18
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,392,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39108
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F391A1778245867
OL,3,CWhat went wrong for Labour in the
OL,4,CNorth West?
OL,6,FThere were tears in Salford as Labour
OL,7,Fcouncillor Teresa Pepper lost her seat
OL,8,Fto Reform UK. She was hugged by
OL,9,Fcolleagues before leaving the count.
OL,10,FHowever, there were hugs and cheers at
OL,11,Fthe Salford City Council count as
OL,12,FLabour held the Eccles ward with 1,663
OL,13,Fvotes to Reform's 1,207.
OL,15,FRebecca Long-Bailey, MP for Salford
OL,16,Fwas at the count in the city, and
OL,17,Fwarned the results would be 'repeated'
OL,18,Fat a General Election, without a
OL,19,F'change in direction'.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/18
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,392,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39109
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F391A1778245867
OL,3,CWhat went wrong for Labour in the
OL,4,CNorth West?
OL,6,FShe told Good Morning Britain: "I
OL,7,Fblame everybody at the top, I think we
OL,8,Fneed to see a real change in direction
OL,9,Fhere. We made some serious mistakes
OL,10,Fearly on, not removing the two child
OL,11,Fcap on Universal Credit when we should
OL,12,Fhave done, now we're in the right
OL,13,Fplace on that, but we shouldn't have
OL,14,Fhad to be dragged to help starving
OL,15,Fchildren and families."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/18
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,392,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39110
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F391A1778245867
OL,3,CWhat went wrong for Labour in the
OL,4,CNorth West?
OL,6,F"Taking the winter fuel allowance off
OL,7,Fpensioners was another thing that no
OL,8,Flabour government should ever have
OL,9,Fdone, cutting disability benefits for
OL,10,Fthose who genuinely couldn't work.. we
OL,11,Fhave to stop doing these sorts of
OL,12,Fthings and start representing our
OL,13,Fcommunities in the way that they
OL,14,Fexpect a Labour government to."
OL,16,FEarlier, the first council to complete
OL,17,Fits count was Halton in Cheshire,
OL,18,Fwhich saw Labour lose 15 seats and
OL,19,FReform gain 15. But with only a third
OL,20,Fof its seats up for grabs, Labour's
OL,21,Flarge majority in Halton remained.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G10/18
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,392,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39111
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F391A1778245867
OL,3,CWhat went wrong for Labour in the
OL,4,CNorth West?
OL,6,FWigan, represented in Parliament by
OL,7,FCulture Secretary Lisa Nandy, also saw
OL,8,FLabour lose 20 seats and Reform gain
OL,9,F23, but the authority remains Labour-
OL,10,Fcontrolled.
OL,12,FChorley saw Reform UK surge to become
OL,13,Fthe official opposition. Labour
OL,14,Fretained overall control of the
OL,15,Fauthority, because only a third of
OL,16,Fseats were up for grabs.
OL,18,FThat meant it was mathematically
OL,19,Fimpossible for the party ` which has
OL,20,Frun the borough since 2012 ` to lose
OL,21,Fits grip on power
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G11/18
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
