OL,3,CWhat went wrong for Labour in the
OL,4,CNorth West?
OL,6,FSir Keir has already faced speculation
OL,7,Fabout his position, with the Times
OL,8,Freporting Energy Secretary and former
OL,9,Fleader Ed Miliband had urged the Prime
OL,10,FMinister to set out a timetable for
OL,11,Fhis departure.
OL,13,FBut Deputy Prime Minister David Lammy
OL,14,Furged his party not to play "pass the
OL,15,Fparcel" with the leadership in
OL,16,Fresponse to the election results.
OL,18,FAnd Defence Secretary John Healey said
OL,19,FSir Keir should be given more time,
OL,20,Fsaying "he can still turn it round".
OL,26,@vD@]OUwD@GO]|D@HOU|D@cO]
